    "comment": "Rationale: Extracellular field recordings in hippocampal slices from Munc13-2 KO mice.\n\nFigure 1 shows an impaired input-output curves indicating impaired synaptic transmission at mossy fiber synapses in the absence of Munc13-2. Synaptic transmission at the Schaffer-collateral synapses recorded in stratum radiatum of area CA1 is not impaired.\nFigure 2 shows that the loss of Munc13-2 leads to increased failures in mossy fiber synaptic transmission.\nFigure 3 shows increased short-term synaptic plasticity in Munc13-2 KO mossy fiber synapses.\nFigure 6 shows that the loss of Munc13-2 leads to a reduction in release probability at mossy fiber synapses.. Experimental description: hippocampal slices were. prepared from littermate wild-type (WT) and Munc13-2-/- (KO) mice, aged between postnatal days P 18-35. The mice were previously described (Varoqueaux et al., 2002).",
